{# Template: monogenic_ntr.md.j2
   ClinGen new gene-disease term request.

   Render with Jinja2 and POST the result as a GitHub issue body.
   The markdown section is human-readable; the YAML section is machine-parseable.

   Required variables:
     submitters        - list of ORCID or ClinGen affiliation URLs
     gene_name         - HGNC gene symbol (e.g. "FZD4")
     hgnc_id           - HGNC numeric ID (e.g. "4042")
     gene_disease_refs - list of references (e.g. ["PMID:12345"])
     parents           - list of dicts with keys: label, id, ref (ref optional)
     term_label        - preferred label for the new term

   Optional variables:
     synonyms          - list of synonym strings
     label_refs        - list of references for label/synonyms
     definition        - definition text
     definition_refs   - list of references for definition
     xrefs             - list of cross-references (e.g. ["OMIM:133780"])
     children          - list of dicts with keys: label, id, ref (ref optional)
     comments          - free-text additional comments

   Suggested issue title: "[ClinGen NTR] {gene_name}-related {disease}"
   Suggested issue labels: ["ClinGen", "New term request"]

Use this form to request a new gene-related disease term for Mondo on behalf of a ClinGen gene curation group.

Mondo follows the naming pattern: `{GENE}-related {disease description}`.
The default definition pattern is: *"Any {parent disease} in which the cause of the disease is a variation in the gene {GENE}."*

